{title: Yours Love}
{artist: Waylon Jennings}
{composer: Written by Harlan Howard}

[3/4 time]
[G]May the fruit of my toil [D7]be yours love
May the fruit from my soil be [G]yours love
And from this moment on may a [C]love that is strong
And [D7]lives on and on be yours [G]love
May the sons that I raise [D7]be yours love
May the comforts I praise be [G]yours love
If I ever get weak may the [C]love words I speak
And [D7]the arms that I seek be yours [G]love
May the [C]Lord's shining grace be [G]yours love
May the [C]happiest face be [D7]yours love
May the [G]last fingertips that [C]touch these two lips
As [D7]life from me slips be yours [G]love